Need assistance from L3 team:
&nbsp;
Case: Adult Signature missing on FedEx labels
&nbsp;
Details:
Customer was using MCSL from April 2024 and was able to generate FedEx labels with Adult Signature. However, after migrating to FedEx REST API, the labels are no longer reflecting Adult Signature.
&nbsp;
We have verified the following:
  Automation rules are updated with Adult Signature enabled  Products were updated via CSV with Adult Signature  In “Edit Special Features,” Adult Signature is shown as selected  &nbsp;
However, the issue persists:
  When labels are generated, Adult Signature is not applied  In request/response, it shows service default  In product settings, “Delivery Confirmation” shows enabled, but FedEx® Delivery Signature Options(Rest) is None  &nbsp;
It appears that the Delivery Confirmation field in the CSV may not be aligned with FedEx REST API, and may be mapped for Web Services instead.
&nbsp;
Could you please review and provide your input?
&nbsp;
If possible, please assist in updating all products with:
  Delivery Confirmation = True  Adult Signature&nbsp;  &nbsp;
Expected results - generate FedEx labels with adult signature required service
&nbsp;
Store Details:
  Store URL: grapebottle.myshopify.com   Account ID: cbbf7ccb-3c7e-41c8-8018-b24277bba64d&nbsp;  &nbsp;
Short recording video - &nbsp;https://drive.google.com/file/d/1bSuoYeGJgRYdvc2WQQQr1WQMpwwU_Bq3/view?usp=sharing

